  section.section-box.mt-50.mb-50
    .container
      .content-detail
        .row
          .col-lg-2
          .col-lg-8
            h2#overview.text-heading-4 Four Year College Degree
            p.text-body-text
              | The Bachelor of Arts in Ministry degree (B.A.Min.) is designed for persons who wish to gain a breadth of ministry skills and knowledge in order to serve as ministers, counselors, educators or in supportive roles for the mission of the church and the redemptive work of God in this world.
            p.text-body-text
              | The degree is based on a strong general studies component and advanced studies in Bible, theology, and ministry principles. Depending on the chosen major, the B.A.Min. degree is designed to prepare students for work as pastors, deacons, ministers of church music, counselors, and educators as well as prepare students for graduate work in the church.
        .row
          .col-lg-2
          .col-lg-8
            h2#majors.text-heading-4.mt-30 Majors
            p.text-body-text
              | The Bachelor of Arts in Ministry (B.A.Min.) degree is composed of three components: the General Education Core, the Bible and Theology Core, and a selected major. Students may choose from the following major areas of study
            ul
              li
                a(href='/majors/bible-and-theology/') Bible and Theology
              li
                a(href='/majors/christian-educational-ministries/') Christian Educational Ministries
              li
                a(href='/majors/counseling-for-christian-ministries/') Counseling for Christian Ministries
              li
                a(href='/majors/hispanic-pastoral-ministries/') Hispanic Pastoral Ministries
              li
                a(href='/majors/leadership-and-ethics/') Leadership and Ethics
              li
                a(href='/majors/pastoral-leadership/') Pastoral Leadership
              li
                a(href='/majors/pastoral-ministries/') Pastoral Ministries
        .row
          .col-lg-2
          .col-lg-8
            h2#minors.text-heading-4.mt-30 Minors
            p.text-body-text
              | In addition, a student may fulfill the requirements for one of the following minor areas of study:
            ul
              li
                a(href='/minors/christian-educational-ministries/') Christian Educational Ministries
              li
                a(href='/minors/leadership-and-ethics/') Leadership and Ethics
              li
                a(href='/minors/pastoral-ministries/') Pastoral Ministries
            .border-bottom.mt-50

  section.section-box.overflow-visible.mb-50
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-10.mx-auto
          .bg-6.box-newsletter.position-relative
            .content-detail
              span.text-body-capitalized.color-gray-500.text-uppercase degree requirements
              h4.text-heading-2.mb-10.mt-10 Traditional Degree Structure
              p.text-body-text.color-gray-500
              | The baccalaureate degree in the traditional degree structure at Nazarene Bible College contains the following degree requirements:
              ul
                li Completion of a minimum of 120 semester hours depending on the major.
                li At least 25% of the semester hours must be in residence, with at least 50% of the final 25% of the program hours in residence. Online classes are considered "in residence."
                li A cumulative GPA of at least 2.0 on a 4.0 scale.
                li A 2.0 GPA in the major with the following program additions/exceptions:
                li Counseling (CC/CCM): 3.0 cumulative GPA for all courses specific to the major.
                li Completion of the required hours in the following areas:
                li General Education Core
                li Bible and Theology Core
                li Major Courses
                li Electives or Minor Courses—Elective courses are courses supplemental to those required for the completion of a degree program. Elective courses can be courses from NBC’s General Education core, Bible and Theology core, AdVantage core, the college’s major and minor programs, or comparable courses transferred from accredited institutions. Career and technical courses from accredited institutions may be applicable as electives for some of NBC’s degree programs.
                li Completion of NBC Experience.
                li Completion of the Ministry Progress Review.
                li Completion of Graduating Colloquium.

  section.section-box.mb-50
    .container
