          .col-lg-8
            h3.text-heading-4.mb-20 Core Requirements and Objectives
        .row
          .col-lg-2
          .col-lg-8
            h4.text-heading-5.mb-20 General Education Core
            p.text-body-text
              strong Objectives
            p.text-body-text
              | Through General Education, Nazarene Bible College encourages the acquisition of foundational knowledge, skills, and values essential for Lifelong Learning and preparation for in-depth study within chosen majors. Students will experience courses in four areas of study: Spiritual Foundations, Communication, Basic Knowledge, and Social Science/Humanities
            p.text-body-text
              | Completion of the General Education core should enable students to:
              ul
                li Engage in intentional spiritual growth toward a Christ-like character and life of service.
                li Demonstrate effective communication skills.
                li Exhibit an understanding of the scientific method and mathematical principles.
                li Analyze traditional and evolving views of women, race, and ethnicity in the US. and abroad.
                li Examine civilization in a global context with emphasis on the history of Christianity and evangelism.
                li Apply the basic principles of Christian ethics in modern society.
        .row
          .col-lg-2
          .col-lg-8
            h4.text-heading-5.mb-20 General Education Core Courses
            p.text-body-text
