            .content-detail
              span.text-body-capitalized.color-gray-500.text-uppercase degree requirements
              h4.text-heading-2.mb-10.mt-10 AdVantage Accelerated Degree Structure
              p.text-body-text
              | The Advantage Program Bachelor of Arts in Ministry degree contains the following degree requirements:
              ul
                li Completion of a minimum of 120 semester hours.
                li At least 30 semester hours in residence.
                li A cumulative GPA of 2.0 on a 4.0 scale with the following program additions/exceptions:
                  ul
                    li Christian School Education: 3.0 cumulative GPA for all EDU courses.
                    li Counseling (CC/CCM): 3.0 cumulative GPA for all courses specific to the major.
                li Completion of the required hours in the following areas:
                  ul
                    li General Education - 45 semester hours
                    li Electives - 15 semester hours
                    li Bible and Theology - 20 semester hours
                    li Foundational - 8 semester hours
                    li Major Courses - 32 semester hours
                li Completion of the capstone project (Leadership and Ethics), student teaching (Christian School Education), Internship, Orientation/Capstone Intensives (Counseling for Christian Ministries).
                li Completion of NBC Experience.
                li Completion of Ministry Progress Review.
                li Completion of Graduating Colloquium.

